folder: Burke Avenue & Mickle Avenue, Bronx, NY
text:
Burke Ave., at Mickle Ave. W.P.A. men are shown constructing a barrier near an embankment leading down to the tracks of the New York, Westchester and Boston Railroad. The houses in the background are on Mickle Ave; on the east side of the tracks.
November 12, 1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
